desc: You must visit this viral valley in China this 2024 🏮 This is📍Wangxian Valley, Jiangxi, China, a newly built scenic spot inspired by the Chinese ancient town architecture. This might not be a real ancient town but is a perfect place to travel in China for documenting, taking photos and fly your drone. How to get there? 🚄 2.5 hours Shanghai to Shangrao + 1 hour by car 🏨 Only two hotels inside the scenic area and more options at the nearest town. 💲Entrance ticket is 100rmb 🕣 Open hours 8:00-22:00 ☀️Best time to go: Spring and autumn, during summer can be very hot and crowded. Also avoid national holidays. 🏩 Looking for hotels? Send me a DM and l share the hotel I stayed at (no collaborations) and other options for foreigners. desc: 3 old towns in China that you must visit in 2024🏮 pt1 What to know 👇 -Nanxun Old Town is a beautiful water town not far from Shanghai. Is perfect for a weekend trip.  You can stop one night in Huzhou to experience the free fireworks show on Friday and Saturday. - Furong Old Town, is the famous waterfall village. Spend one night at this place to experience the lantern decorations. - Fenghuang Old Town, is one of the most beautiful old towns in China. I recommend staying two days and one night at least to experience the local life. * I often recommend visiting Furong & Fenghuang in combination with Zhangjiajie. desc: ad Only the most beautiful place I have ever seen 🥹🇨🇳 This is the Yunnan province in China and it quite simply took my breath away 🤯✈️🏔️ Here are things to do and places to see during your trip to China: 🏘️ Explore the Ancient towns of the Yunnan region. My personal highlights were Dali and Lijiang 🧊 When in Lijiang head to the trendy cocktail bar ‘The Clouds Headin’ and stroll through the magical streets during sunset 🍜 Eat the local food. I personally loved the traditional Chinese round table lunches and don’t miss the famous ‘Crossing the Bridge Noodles’ (I’ll be making a dedicated food in China video soon) 🏔️ Spend a half day in the stunning Blue Moon Valley. It’s one of the most beautiful places on earth 🥹 ❤️ Immerse yourself in the local culture and learn about the Chinese ethnic minorities living in the Yunnan province. For instance you could shop some tie dye clothes from the Bai people who are a local ethnic group ☕️ When having the local coffee - try raw coconut lattes, mine may have been the best coffee I ever had! 😅🤯 The best place for coffee shops is Panxi Village on the Erhai lake if you ask me 🚲 Visit the stunning Erhai lake. You can do a cycling tour or just take some photos but don’t miss adding this to your China itinerary @China Now #nihaochina #nihaoyunnan #nihaolijiang #nihaodali #tripcom #travelwithtripcom #yunnanprovince #yunnanchina #lijiang #lijiangoldtown #lijiangyunnan #lijiangtravel #chinatrip #placestovisit #placestogo #placestotravel #placestosee #places_wow #beautifulplaces #beautifulplacestotravel #beautifulplacestovisit 🇨🇳✈️😍
